08:56.503 --> 09:00.872
>> Ohhh....
>> Gumball: Huh? Oh. Sorry!
>> [ Sighs ]

09:00.874 --> 09:01.873
>> Ow!

09:13.953 --> 09:19.724
Uuuuuuuuuuugh!
>> Dad: Show yourself, ghost of
Mr. Robinson!

09:19.726 --> 09:26.398
[ Whirrrrrrr! ]
[ Thunk! ]
Hey, what's up, neighbor?

09:26.400 --> 09:32.103
>> I've had enough of this
family!
Your tacky lifestyle, your ugly

09:32.105 --> 09:38.443
house, your cheap garden shed!
I'll smash it to pieces!
[ Grunting ]

09:42.715 --> 09:46.952
[ Panting ]
It's more solid than i thought.
But this is what i do to your

09:46.954 --> 09:51.189
unfashionable deck chairs!
Unh! Uggh!
[ Grunting ]

09:51.191 --> 09:55.026
Gosh darn it!
[ Panting ]
And as for your crummy

09:55.028 --> 10:02.367
thrift store vacuum cleaner --
buy cheap...
Buy twice!

10:02.369 --> 10:12.444
And this is what i think of your
$2 clip-on tie!
[ Laughs maniacally ]

10:12.446 --> 10:19.718
I'm back!
And as for you...
[ Growls ]

10:19.720 --> 10:26.257
[ Both chuckle, grumble ]
>> Both: Yay!
Welcome back, Mr. Robinson!

10:26.259 --> 10:29.728
>> Thanks.
>> Gumball: So, since we saved
your marriage and everything, i

10:29.730 --> 10:32.731
guess that makes us best friends
forever?
>> Darwin: So can we call you

10:32.733 --> 10:40.205
gaylord instead of Mr. Robinson?
>> don't push it, kid.
Now, take me home, woman.

10:40.207 --> 10:42.173
>> [ Chuckles ]

10:44.343 --> 10:47.412
>> Dad: What was that all about?
>> Gumball: Well, there never
was a ghost, dad.

10:47.414 --> 10:50.348
>> Darwin: It was Mr. Robinson.
>> Gumball: We hid him in the
attic.

10:50.350 --> 10:54.753
>> Dad: No.
I mean, what's wrong with our
house, our shed, and my tie?

10:54.755 --> 10:57.522
[ Sniffles ]
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]
Dad, you know what i do when i

10:57.524 --> 11:01.726
